'''Al-Kawthar TV''' is a [[Tehran]]-based [[Arabic language|Arabic]]-language television channel. Launched in 2006 by [[Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting]], it broadcasts religious and cultural programs about 20 hours a day mainly for [[Arab]] audience in the [[Middle East]] and [[North Africa]]. The content of the programs is mainly about promoting [[Shia Islam]]. The TV station derives its name from the heavenly river [[Al-Kawthar]].
