{{Infobox video game |title=ColorZ |image=ColorZ Coverart.png |caption= |developer=[[Exkee]] |publisher=Exkee |designer= |engine= |released={{vgrelease|EU|July 24, 2009|NA|September 7, 2009|JP|November 30, 2010}} |genre=[[Action game|Action]], [[Puzzle video game|Puzzle]] |modes=[[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer]] |platforms=[[Wii]] }}
'''''ColorZ''''' is an [[Action game|action]]/[[puzzle video game]] for [[WiiWare]] by [[Exkee]]. It was released in Europe on July 24, 2009,<ref>[http://gonintendo.com/viewstory.php?id=88761 ColorZ will be available the 24th of July]</ref> North America on September 7, 2009,<ref>{{cite web |title=From Faraway Galaxies to the Family Room, Start Fall on a Fun-Filled Foot |url=https://www.nintendo.com/whatsnew/detail/981Bra1xi5r009C5WDmn-Ktolso3-MEO |publisher=Nintendo of America |date=7 September 2009 |accessdate=9 September 2009}}</ref> and Japan on November 30, 2010.<ref>{{cite web | script-title=ja:カラーズ |trans-title=ColorZ | url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/wiiware/wczj/index.html | publisher=Nintendo Co. Ltd | language=Japanese | accessdate=December 7, 2010}}</ref>
==Gameplay== The game is set in a world polluted by microbes of different colors, which the player must clean up by absorbing them into a UFO. Players control up to 3 UFOs colored red, green and blue that individually can only absorb microbes of their own color. However, by fusing together their UFOs, players can absorb other colors based on additive [[color mixing]]. For example, to absorb yellow microbes the red and green UFOs must fuse, while a fusion of all three UFOs will allow the player to absorb white microbes. Players must also avoid absorbing the wrong colored microbe with their UFOs. The game also features a co-operative mode for up to three players that sees each player controlling an individual UFO.<ref>[http://wiiware.nintendolife.com/games/wiiware/colorz Nintendo Life ColorZ profile]</ref>
The game is controlled with the [[Wii Remote]] and Nunchuk in single player, though only the Wii Remote is required in multiplayer.<ref name=NLinterview/>
==Development== The color matching and absorbing aspects of the game was inspired by the [[shoot 'em up]] ''[[Ikaruga]]''.<ref name=NLinterview>[http://wiiware.nintendolife.com/news/2009/07/interviews_colorz_exkee Interviews: ColorZ - Exkee]</ref>
