==2018 labor strike==
On February 14, 2018, a statement was released through Le Syndicat des Travailleurs et Travailleuses du Jeu Vidéo (STJV, Union of Video Game Workers) in which 21 out of 44 workers claimed that Eugen Systems had denied overtime pay, delayed paychecks, reduced gross wages below French minimum wage requirements, and failed to honor contractual and collectively bargained obligations, and that they were [[Strike action|going on strike]] until their demands were met. Eugen Systems released a statement denying the majority of these allegations, but admitting to two instances of delayed payrolls due to technical issues, rather than malicious intent. STJV set up a [[crowdfunding]] campaign to raise money to support the employees on strike.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bell|first1=Brian|title=Employees of French Videogame Developer Eugen Systems Go on Strike|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/02/employees-of-french-videogame-developer-eugen-syst.html|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=Paste Magazine|date=15 February 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Perricone|first1=Marcello|title=Eugen Systems Employees Are On Strike Due To Work Conditions And La... {{!}} GameWatcher|url=https://www.gamewatcher.com/news/2018-16-02-developers-of-steel-division-are-on-strike|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=Game Watcher|date=19 February 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sinclair|first1=Brendan|title=Eugen Systems employees on strike|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-02-15-eugen-systems-employees-on-strike|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=GamesIndustry.biz|date=15 February 2018|language=en}}</ref> A statement from STJV a week later indicated that the strike was representative of a deeper lack of respect within the video game industry of programmers' experience and other abilities.<ref>{{cite web|title=Eugen Systems strike workers are holding on – STJV|url=https://www.stjv.fr/en/2018/02/eugen-systems-strike-workers-are-holding-on/|website=Le Syndicat des Travailleurs et Travailleuses du Jeu Vidéo|accessdate=29 March 2018|date=21 February 2018}}</ref> Employees who were on strike met at each other's homes to support each other and plan meetings with the press, labor advocates, and politicians.<ref name="Kotaku Strike 1 Month">{{cite news|last1=Gach|first1=Ethan|title=Developers At One French Game Studio Have Been On Strike For A Month|url=https://kotaku.com/developers-at-one-french-game-studio-have-been-on-strik-1823833426|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=Kotaku|date=16 March 2018}}</ref>

Staff representative Félix Habert stated that it took two weeks for Eugen Systems leadership to approached him and others to resolve the issue and the first meeting did not take place until March 5.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tarason|first1=Dominic|title=Nearly a month on, Eugen Systems staff remain on strike|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/03/12/nearly-a-month-on-eugen-systems-staff-remain-on-strike/|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|date=12 March 2018}}</ref><ref name="Kotaku Strike 1 Month"/>  A statement from STJV about this meeting stated that Eugen Systems denied that the employees' contracts were accurate or enforceable, and that the following day they sent a proposal for ending the strike that was "incomplete" and "not serious."<ref name="Kotaku Strike 1 Month"/>

French Deputy [[Sébastien Leclerc (politician)|Sébastien Leclerc]] spoke out against the strike in favor of Eugen Systems, saying that the strike was motivated by the "political positioning" of the strikers and calling it a "hostage taking".<ref>{{cite web|title=Question n°6124 - Assemblée nationale|url=http://questions.assemblee-nationale.fr/q15/15-6124QE.htm|website=Assemblée Nationale|accessdate=29 March 2018|language=fr-FR|date=6 March 2018|quote=La grève qui a débuté le 14 février 2018 au sein de l'entreprise Eugen Systems semble, sous couvert de revendications liées à leur condition salariale, motivée par un positionnement politique de ces grévistes. […] Il regrette l'impact que ces mouvements ont sur l'activité de l'entreprise Eugen Systems, entreprise française indépendante, ayant fait ses preuves depuis vingt ans dans un secteur hautement concurrentiel et il lui demande quelles mesures elle compte prendre pour mettre fin à cette prise en otage de ladite société.}}</ref> [[Le Monde]] later revealed that Leclerc and the wife of the CEO of Eugen Systems knew each other very well and that she was one of his supporters during his 2017 election campaign, creating a conflict of interest in dealing with the strike.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Audureau|first1=William|last2=Baruch|first2=Jérémie|title=Un député LR soupçonné de conflit d’intérêts après avoir critiqué une grève dans le jeu vidéo|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/pixels/article/2018/03/15/un-depute-lr-soupconne-de-conflit-d-interets-apres-avoir-critique-une-greve-dans-le-jeu-video_5271238_4408996.html|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=Le Monde.fr|date=13 March 2018|language=fr}}</ref>

On April 3, 2018, the strike was ended by employees saying: "We do not think we will gain any additional ground with this strike, despite the fact our grievances are simply about conforming to labour laws and collective labour agreements". Fifteen of the 21 employees sought to take their grievances to the French [[Labour Court (France)|Labour Court]]. The website for collecting donations was shut down a few days after this announcement. <ref>{{cite news |last1=O'Connor |first1=Alice |title=Eugen Systems strike is over but the fight continues |url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/04/13/eugen-systems-end-strike/ |accessdate=24 September 2018 |work=Rock Paper Shotgun |date=13 April 2018}}</ref>

