{{Infobox person |name = Jean-Pierre Foucault |image = Salon_du_livre_-_Michel_Foucault.jpg |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1947|11|23|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Marseille]], [[France]] |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = Television and radio presenter |nationality = French }} '''Jean-Pierre Foucault''' (born 23 November 1947 in [[Marseille]]) is a French television and radio host. He was born in Marseille, his mother was Jewish. He was the host of ''[[Qui Veut Gagner des Millions ?]]'', the French version of ''[[Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?]]'', and the host of ''Zone Rouge'', the French version of ''[[The Chair (game show)|The Chair]]''. He has been hosting the [[Miss France]] pageant since 1996 and hosted [[Miss Europe 2006]] pageant.
Foucault played himself in the 2006 film [[My Best Friend (2006 film)|''Mon Meilleur Ami'']] directed by [[Patrice Leconte]] and starring [[Dany Boon]] as a taxi driver who wins the top prize in ''[[Qui Veut Gagner des Millions?]]''. Foucault shares his life with Evelyn Jarre without being married. He has a daughter from a previous marriage, Virginia Foucault.
