'''Kkehna Hai Kuch Mujhko'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2004/20040314/spectrum/tv.htm|title=The Sunday Tribune - Spectrum - Television|website=www.tribuneindia.com|access-date=2016-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/old-html/special/y2k4/boxpopuli16.htm|title=Singing a different tune - Indiantelevision dot com's Box Populi by Subhash K Jha|website=www.indiantelevision.com|access-date=2016-06-23}}</ref> was a TV series by [[Balaji Telefilms]], broadcast on [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony Entertainment Television]], from 11 March 2004 to 2005. It aired Friday to Sunday 8:30 PM
The serial showed [[Pallavi Joshi]] as protagonist Reva Kapoor, and her journey from a dutiful wife and mother to a working woman.
Swapna Waghmare Joshi was the director of the serial and script was by Mushtaq Shaikh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/headlines/y2k4/mar/mar26.htm|title='Kkehna...' to add beef to Sony weekend lineup|website=Indian Television Dot Com|access-date=2016-06-23}}</ref>
== Plot == Reva has been a devoted mother and dutiful wife all her life. She has always put her own ambitions on the back burner, while dealing with demanding kids and a controlling husband. She decides to join work and find her identity as an individual. She has a supportive mother-in-law (Surekha Sikri) and friend (Ronit Roy as Ishan) who help her out in this quest. However, problems in her errant children's life and her husband's (Nishchay Kapoor, played by Kiran Karmarkar) extra-marital affair complicate things.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Ekta-Kapoor-Ajeeb-Daastaan-hai-ye-will-be-an-important-story-in-the-evolution-of-TV/articleshow/44502743.cms|title=Ekta Kapoor: Ajeeb Daastaan hai ye will be an important story in the evolution of TV - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2016-06-23}}</ref>
