{{Infobox person | name = Nai Bonet | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = January 1945 | birth_place = [[Saigon]], [[Vietnam]] | death_date = | death_place = | years_active = 1964&ndash;1980 | spouse = }}
'''Nai Bonet''' is a [[Vietnam]]ese [[Belly dance|belly-dancer]], singer and film actress. Born in Saigon to a Vietnamese mother and French father,<ref>{{cite news|title=Belly Dance -- in Opera'|work=[[Tucson Daily Citizen]]|date=February 14, 1966}}</ref> Bonet began her professional career at age 13, when she headlined as a belly-dancer in a show at the [[Flamingo Hotel]] in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]].<ref name="Biography">{{cite press release|publisher=Compass International, Inc|year=1979|title=Nocturna - Nai Bonet Biography}}</ref> She began appearing in films in 1964 (frequently portraying a belly-dancer), as well as in television, commercials, variety shows, her photos adorned several album covers and she continued to appear as a night club headliner. In 1966 she released the novelty song ''Jelly Belly'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rateyourmusic.com/release/single/nai_bonet/jelly_belly___the_seventh_veil/|title=''Jelly Belly/The Seventh Veil - Rate Your Music''|accessdate=2011-06-27}}</ref> and she filmed a music video for the song<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1SVs_CrzJiQ|title=''YouTube - Nai Bonet - Jelly Belly music video''|accessdate=2011-06-27}}</ref> which was featured on [[Scopitone]] video [[jukeboxes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scopitonearchive.com/scopitones/by_artist/a_b.html|title=''Scopitones by Artist: A to B''|accessdate=2011-06-27}}</ref>
In the 1970s, Bonet decided to focus exclusively on her acting career, "But I wasn't getting anywhere in pictures," she said in 1978.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wilson|first=Earl|title=Belly Dancer in Dracula Film?|work=Daily Intelligencer|date=September 30, 1978}}</ref> After conceiving, producing and starring in two film flops (1979's ''[[Nocturna: Granddaughter of Dracula|Nocturna]]'' and 1980's ''Hoodlums''), Bonet gave up her career.
