{{Infobox politician |name = Sara Skyttedal |image = Almedalen 2014 (17550250022).jpg |image_size = 200 |caption = Skyttedal in 2014 |alt = |birth_name = Sara Magdalena Skyttedal |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|8|6|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Tyresö]], Sweden |nationality = Swedish |party = [[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Christian Democrats]] }}
'''Sara Magdalena Skyttedal''' (born 6 August 1986) is a Swedish politician for the [[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Christian Democrats]] party. Between 2013 and 2016, she chaired the [[Young Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Young Christian Democrats]]. Since 2016 she is a [[municipal commissioner]] for [[Linköping]].
==Career== In September 2002 Skyttedal became a member of the Young Christian Democrats.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.expressen.se/kvallsposten/sara-skyttedal-utsatt-for-sabotage-i-vaxjo/|title=Sara Skyttedal utsatt för sabotage i Växjö|work=[[Expressen]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> Since then, she has been chairperson of the Haninge constituance for the party, and ombudsman for district group in Stockholm's municipality.<ref name="dn.se">{{cite web|url=http://fokus.dn.se/sara-skyttedal-kd-maste-komma-ut-som-akta-hoger/|title=Sara Skyttedal: KD måste komma ut som äkta höger|work=[[Dagens Nyheter]]|date=27 May 2016|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> She has been district director for the Christian Democrats for Stockholm and vice chairperson for the party in [[Haninge Municipality|Haninge]].<ref name="aftonbladet.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/samhalle/article23231826.ab|title=KDU-ordföranden Sara Skyttedal avgår|work=[[Aftonbladet]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref>
Skyttedal studied political science, political economy and history science at [[Stockholm University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dagen.se/sara-skyttedal-vill-ge-sverige-en-rak-hoger-1.375223|title=Sara Skyttedal vill ge Sverige en rak höger|work=[[Dagen (Swedish newspaper)|Dagen]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> She has also studied rhetoric, Swedish and law.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagen.se/sara-skyttedal-vill-ge-sverige-en-rak-hoger-1.375223 |title=Sara Skyttedal vill ge sverige en rak höger |work=Dagen |accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> Skyttedal participated in the beauty pageant [[Nya Fröken Sverige|Miss Sweden]] in 2006,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smp.se/nyheter/vaxjo-tjej-vidare-i-nya-froken-sverige/|title=Växjö tjej vidare i Nya fröken Sverige |work=[[Smålandsposten]]|first=Ingen|last=Ingen|date=20 March 2006|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> where she made the Top 15 in the final. It was her fiancé that sent in an application for her to compete.<ref name="dn.se"/>
Skyttedal has a background in municipality politics for [[Haninge]], until 2010 she was first vice chairperson in the adult education and high school board and as well as juryman in [[Södertörn]]'s court.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haninge.se/upload/21981/kommunorganisation.pdf |publisher=[[Haninge Municipality]] |title=Kommunorganisation |date=19 May 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124132225/http://haninge.se/upload/21981/kommunorganisation.pdf |archivedate=24 November 2010|language=sv}}</ref>
At the 2010 general elections in Sweden, she was a replacement at the Haninge City council, a job she was released from in early 2011 when she moved from the municipality.<ref name="auto"/> At the 2009 and 2014 elections for the European parliament, Skyttedal was a candidate for her party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.val.se/val/ep2009/slutresultat/personroster.html|title=Personröster|year=2009|publisher=[[Valmyndigheten]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090608173610/http://www.val.se/val/ep2009/slutresultat/personroster.html|archivedate=8 June 2009|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.svt.se/opinion/lat-effektivitet-bli-en-ny-ledstjarna-for-eu|title=Debattartikel: Låt effektivitet bli en ny ledstjärna för EU|first=Sara|last=Skyttedal|publisher=[[Sveriges Television]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> At the 2010 general elections she became candidate for the municipality elections in Stockholm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.val.se/val/val2010/slutresultat/R/rvalkrets/02/personroster.html|title=Stockholms län - Personröster|year=2010|publisher=[[Election Authority (Sweden)|Election Authority]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> She has also resided in [[Växjö]] and was part of the 2014 general election for the Kronoberg constituency.<ref name="auto"/>
Skyttedal has been the chairperson of Young Christian Democrats since 11 May 2013 and a member of the Christian Democrats party executive board. She was previously first vice chairperson for the Young Christian Democrats.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kristdemokraterna.se/VartParti/KontaktaOss/Partistyrelse |publisher=[[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Christian Democrats]] |title=Partistyrelsen |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403234210/http://www.kristdemokraterna.se/VartParti/KontaktaOss/Partistyrelse |archivedate=3 April 2012 |language=sv}}</ref> From May 2011 to May 2015, she was the vice chairperson for the [[Youth of the European People's Party]] (YEPP).<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.kdu.se/Pressochmedia/saraskyttedalvaldtillviceiyepp |title=Sara Skyttedal vald till vice ordförande i Yepp |publisher=[[Young Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Kristdemokratiska Ungdomsförbundet]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111016014258/http://www.kdu.se/Pressochmedia/saraskyttedalvaldtillviceiyepp |archivedate=16 October 2011|language=sv}}</ref>
In October 2015, Skyttedal became the pivotal factor in the Christian Democrats' decision to pull out of the controversial December Agreement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20151009/swedish-party-votes-to-quit-budget-deal|title=Fears deal collapse could spark Swedish vote|date=9 October 2015|work=[[The Local]]|accessdate=16 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=2054&artikel=6275257|title=Christian Democrats reject December Agreement|publisher=[[Sveriges Radio]]|accessdate=16 October 2016}}</ref>
In July 2016, Skyttedal announced that she would resign as chairperson for the Young Christian Democrats at the next meeting, to be held in late 2016.<ref name="aftonbladet.se" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.svd.se/sara-skyttedal-slutar-som-kdu-ordforande|title=Sara Skyttedal slutar som KDU-ordförande|last=Lundgren|first=Rasmus|work=[[Svenska Dagbladet]]|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> On 8 September 2016, she announced that she had gained the office of municipal commissioner in Linköping.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article23480213.ab|title=Skyttedal om nya uppdraget: Uppenbart inte någon expert|work=Aftonbladet|accessdate=8 September 2016|language=sv}}</ref> In the campaign for the September 2018 election for Linköping city hall, she made her party stand out as the most eager to lower municipal tax,<ref>[http://corren.se/nyheter/linkoping/kd-vill-sanka-skatten-med-en-krona-om4693958.aspx KD vill sänka skatten med en krona], ''[[Östgöta Correspondenten]]'', 8 June 2017.</ref> and gained 7.5% of the votes, which compared to 4.8% in the 2014 election was the largest increase of any party.<ref>[http://corren.se/nyheter/linkoping/skyttedaleffekt-hos-valjarna-om5455310.aspx Skyttedaleffekt hos väljarna], ''[[Östgöta Correspondenten]]'', 10 September 2018.</ref>
