A '''script analyst''', script reader, or story analyst is an individual who reads a [[film script]] to determine the material's desirable and undesirable characteristics as relates to story and [[film production]].<ref>{{cite book |author= Garfinkel, Asher |title= Screenplay Story Analysis |publisher= Allworth Press |year= 2007 |isbn= 978-1-58115-478-8}}</ref> This information is often useful for judging the quality of a script, and analysts often provide feedback and suggestions for improving it.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=p7e5YDLKpxEC&lpg=PT294&dq=%22script%20analyst%22&pg=PT294#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= Screenwriting For Dummies |year= 2011 |publisher= John Wiley & Sons |author= Laura Schellhardt |isbn= 1118052625 |accessdate= 31 December 2014}}</ref>

